To assess how well Stage 2 recovers {\em low-ranked} TPs, we identify the ranking cut-off for R@P50 and count the missing TPs below this threshold---i.e., those misclassified as false negatives.
Even with our best methods, ca. 16% of all the ground-truth O values fall into the category of low-rank missing TPs.